## 3. Deploy Procedure

{% if container == "docker" and orchestrator == "kubernetes" %}
1. Update image tag in Kubernetes deployment manifest
2. Apply manifests: `kubectl apply -f k8s/`
3. Monitor rollout: `kubectl rollout status deployment/{{ project_name }}`
{% elif container == "docker" %}
1. Pull latest Docker image
2. Stop existing container: `docker compose down`
3. Start updated container: `docker compose up -d`
{% else %}
1. Pull latest code on the deployment target
2. Build the application: `{{ build_cmd }}`
3. Restart the application process
{% endif %}

## 4. Post-Deploy Verification

- [ ] Health endpoint responds with 200
- [ ] Application logs show successful startup
- [ ] No error spikes in monitoring dashboards
{% if database_name != "none" %}
- [ ] Database connectivity verified
{% endif %}

## 5. Rollback Procedure

{% if orchestrator == "kubernetes" %}
1. Roll back deployment: `kubectl rollout undo deployment/{{ project_name }}`
2. Verify rollback: `kubectl rollout status deployment/{{ project_name }}`
{% elif container == "docker" %}
1. Stop current container: `docker compose down`
2. Redeploy previous image tag: `docker compose up -d`
{% else %}
1. Revert to previous release commit
2. Rebuild and restart: `{{ build_cmd }}`
{% endif %}
3. Verify health endpoint responds with 200
4. Notify team of rollback

## 6. Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Possible Cause | Action |
|---------|---------------|--------|
| Health check fails | Application not started | Check application logs |
| Connection refused | Port mismatch | Verify port configuration |
| High error rate | Bad deployment | Initiate rollback procedure |
{% if database_name != "none" %}
| Database errors | Migration failure | Check migration status and logs |
{% endif %}

